To get started you'll need some basic resources.
Flint tools are an immediate improvement on your wood and stone alternatives
Mortars offer a more efficient means of producing Gravel, and are required for some Dust recipes later on.
Crop sticks will allow you to mutate crops and improve their yields considerably.
A steady supply of food will be necessary to ensure your survival.
In order to determine the traits of your seeds you'll need a seed analyzer.

Time to hunt for some hives.  Be careful: bees get annoyed when you loiter around their hives, and get VERY annoyed when you break them.  You should try using a Smoker on a hive before breaking it with a Scoop.
Acquire more species for your breeding endeavours.
The forestry analyzer can scan bees and determine their exact traits.
Imperial and Industrial Bees are key to accessing useful resource-generating bees.
You'll need several varieties of ores in order to successfully progress to subsequent tiers.
Iron is necessary for any number of machines and tools. To get Iron, you'll first need to mine some Iron Ore.
There are a number of ways you can create torches.
Imagine that, flint & steel actually requires steel.  To start fires, you may need to assemble a more primitive tool; winding a rope around a stick to spin it quickly may do the trick.

Since you cannot cook logs in a furnace to make charcoal, your best option may be a Charcoal Pit. Charcoal Pits are comprised of wood piles surrounded by solid blocks. Note that some solid blocks yield better results than others.
Demonstrate your mastery of Charcoal Pits. And get rewarded.
One option for increasing your ore yields is a FactoryTech grinder. It will require constant replenishing of parts, but requires no power input.
The first step towards better ore resource yields is producing crushed ores.
Crushed ores can be processed further to get impure dusts.  With the right technology, impure dusts can be centrifuged for byproducts, some of which are rare.
To fill cauldrons and move fluids around, you'll need a bucket.
Impure dusts cannot be used in alloys. To cleanse the dusts, you can throw up to an entire stack of it onto a cauldron with water in it.
You'll need a considerable amount of clay to assemble your first fluid infastructure.

Clay Barrels are a primitive means of storing liquids. To build them you'll need Unfired Clay Barrels.  Smelt the Unfired Clay Barrel to acquire a Clay Barrel, where you can store liquid. These can be combined in a larger structure for more storage capacity.
Porcelain will require some Bone Meal.
Porcelain can be used to build Channels and Faucets, a primitive step above carting water around with buckets.
Channels and faucets are an early-game method to move fluids. You can set these up to transport water to, for example, near your Cauldron.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Right tool for the right job
betterquesting:10.desc:8: There are several tools which you will need to process resources, assemble tools and build machines.
You can significantly increase the duration of iron by cooking it again (as nuggets) into wrought iron.
Need an explosion?  You can craft some early-game explosives if necessary.

Show us that you can use the Object Submission Station
With the wrought iron you've acquired, you can greatly improve the durability of your tools.
Break down your copper and tin ores.
You can improve your ore processing yields considerably with Foundry equipment.
You do not have options to alloy Bronze very effectively at this point; you'll need to acquire some the inefficient way for now.
A modest improvement over Iron, you can improve you industry by smelting Bronze.
It is possible to greatly increase your resource yields by combining some industries together. For instance, machines from FactoryTech and Foundry.
Smelt a goodly number of Iron Ingots. You will need them.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Explode me up before you go
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Almost all Pneumaticraft machinery and items require some amount of Compressed Iron.
The Pneumaticraft Compressor is necessary to generate the compressed air required by certain machines.
The small coal boiler is the most basic method of creating steam. It is reasonably efficient, but does not output very much.
Fluiducts are a massive improvement over ceramic Channels for moving fluids.
An excellent way to generate infinite water is with Water Tanks. They will slowly yield water when water flows above them.
An alternative method of acquiring infinite water is the FactoryTech Water Collector. You need to put this device in the water and it will slowly, but surely collect water for you.
Solar Boilers can be used to generate small amounts of steam essentially for free, so long as the sun is shining. Don't forget to clean them every so often.
Many materials and blocks can only be acquired with the user of something like the Compressor.
The macerator is useful for 'mortaring' resources. Note that early versions (e.g. Steam) are NOT capable of duplicating ores!
The extractor is an efficient way of extracting resources from things like plantlife. This can save considerable time with, for instance, rubber.
Rubber will be very important for progressing into the next age. It is most easily acquired by chopping down rubber trees.
Diamonds can be difficult to find. If necessary, you can make them by compressing coal.
You can generate income by selling Diamonds.
Get the raw ingredients you'll need to produce proper rubber.
Many resources can only be generated in special machines. An alloy smelter is an efficient way to produce things like Bronze, but is also the only early way to acquire Rubber.
In order to build wires you are going to need to acquire rubber, and a lot of it.
Generating steam 'on need' can be inefficient. Storing it can ensure you have what you need when you need it.
You can generate income by selling Bronze.
Improve your smelting efficiency by building a Steam Furnace.
Compressing wrought iron yields a result which is even easier to work into steel, if you're willing to build the infrastruture for it.
At some point you will need to venture into this hellish landscape to acquire more unusual resources.
To progress any further, you will need to produce a new metal: Steel. You will need a great deal of it.
Produce a humongous quantity of Steel. You will need every ounce of it.
Emerge from your cave, brave the world, and discover the secrets of smelting.
